And if you've got a unique skill set that I didn't mention


00:52:57.000 --> 00:53:00.040
or I couldn't even think of, then


00:53:00.040 --> 00:53:01.960
if you come and advertise to us, maybe


00:53:01.960 --> 00:53:04.040
we'll be able to find some creative way where


00:53:04.040 --> 00:53:06.000
we can put that to use.


00:53:06.000 --> 00:53:07.540
Yeah, that's a really interesting way


00:53:07.540 --> 00:53:10.480
to leverage the community, not just the core programming


00:53:10.480 --> 00:53:12.600
skills, but the other stuff as well.


00:53:12.600 --> 00:53:16.480
Yeah, and I think it's really essential that we


00:53:16.480 --> 00:53:17.760
have this kind of approach.


00:53:17.760 --> 00:53:21.040
Because I think the thing that's difficult about running


00:53:21.040 --> 00:53:26.760
a community of volunteers is that if you run a business,


00:53:26.760 --> 00:53:29.680
well, I can buy productivity.


00:53:29.680 --> 00:53:30.680
I pay you.


00:53:30.680 --> 00:53:32.760
You make me something, right?


00:53:32.760 --> 00:53:36.120
But when I have a community of volunteers, I can't pay you.


00:53:36.120 --> 00:53:37.800
I don't have any money to pay you with.


00:53:37.800 --> 00:53:39.880
So the only way I can get you to do something


00:53:39.880 --> 00:53:41.640
is to motivate you.


00:53:41.640 --> 00:53:45.360
And there's some intrinsic motivation


00:53:45.360 --> 00:53:49.520
in being part of something good and wholesome like this.


00:53:49.520 --> 00:53:52.120
I think the culture helps bring people in


00:53:52.120 --> 00:53:54.000
from an altruistic point of view.


00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:55.120
They just want to help out.


00:53:55.120 --> 00:53:58.880
They want to be a good force in the universe.


00:53:58.880 --> 00:54:04.200
But ultimately, if you really want strong, directed


00:54:04.200 --> 00:54:07.440
initiative and motivation, I think


00:54:07.440 --> 00:54:13.800
you have to find a synergy, a sort of a thing


00:54:13.800 --> 00:54:16.520
where your personal goals align with the goals


00:54:16.520 --> 00:54:18.640
of the community, right?


00:54:18.640 --> 00:54:22.360
So you want to do something for us that's good for you,


00:54:22.360 --> 00:54:23.600
but it's also good for us.


00:54:23.600 --> 00:54:25.800
That's the perfect way to motivate people.


00:54:25.800 --> 00:54:28.680
So by providing as many ways as possible for people


00:54:28.680 --> 00:54:30.600
