01:03:49.160 --> 01:03:52.720
So what it does is you make a config file.


01:03:52.720 --> 01:03:55.400
You put connection strings into that config file.


01:03:55.400 --> 01:03:58.360
So say you want to do a backup of Postgres.


01:03:58.360 --> 01:04:01.200
Well, you write a single string that's like Postgres,


01:04:01.200 --> 01:04:04.160
colon, slash, slash, the username, the password.


01:04:04.160 --> 01:04:05.520
And then you put that in there.


01:04:05.520 --> 01:04:07.280
And now it knows how to talk to Postgres.


01:04:07.280 --> 01:04:10.440
It does all of that stuff for you.


01:04:10.440 --> 01:04:13.240
So now you've told it a couple of databases,


01:04:13.240 --> 01:04:16.320
